span.font: An assigned robot enters a room in a hospital to provide the cleaning maintenance procedure of a patient's room. The cleaning task must be performed by achieving the following goals: (i) clean floor - where it vacuums the floor, moves the furniture when necessary and wipes the floor; (ii) maintain bed and bath linen - where it should first attend bed linen procedure, followed by changing bath linen; and (iii) sterilise room - where all furniture and equipment in the room are sterilised. In case of failure in performing any of those goals, the robot should immediately warn the sector management, but does not stop executing.

font.span: Starting from the clean floor goal, the robot realizes that it cannot perform the cleaning without moving some furniture around. So, it warns the management sector that another robot is needed to assist the task of moving the furniture around. Once the assistive robot has arrived to the room, the move furniture goal is pursued. Once that goal is achieved, the originally designated robot pursues the goals to perform vacuum cleaning

[ALTERNATIVE PROCEDURE WILL BE LEFT OUT FOR THE MOMENT] and perform floor wiping. However, given the robot battery level has reached the threshold of 75% mostly due to energy consumption while pursuing the move furniture goal, a partial (essential) floor wiping is performed instead of a full wiping floor procedure. Lastly, so that the clean floor goal can be achieved, the once moved furniture needs to be replaced back into its original position. Naturally, the move furniture procedure can only be pursued if the move furniture goal was achieved successfully.

span.font: The next goal to be pursued in the cleaning maintenance procedure, is to maintain the bed and bath linen. The robots starts from pursuing the bed assessment procedure in case it needs further assistance to change the bed linen. For example, the bed can be in a position where the robot cannot perform the procedure to change the bed linen. In this particular scenario, the bed is appropriately placed in a position where the goal change bed linen can be pursued [I WONDER NOW IF ACHIEVING G8 SHOULD BE PRECONDITION TO G9a TOO].

font.span: As the goal to change the bed linen was achieved, the robot now moves towards the bathroom to pursue the goal of changing the towel linen. Once successfully achieved, the bed and bath linen goal is marked as achieved.
[ALTERNATIVE PROCEDURE OF G9b WILL BE LEFT OUT FOR THE MOMENT]

span.font: The final subgoal to be pursued in the cleaning maintenance procedure is the room sterilisation. However, before pursuing that goal, the mission manager must check if the clean floor goal was successfully achieved. Once this condition was attended, the room sterilisation procedure is pursued and then successfully achieved.
